OL,3,CWife of TV doctor Michael Mosley
OL,4,Caccepts his British Podcast Award
OL,6,FShe added that Mosley knew his podcast
OL,7,F"really connected with people", and
OL,8,F"he loved the simplicity of the format
OL,9,Fand being able to genuinely help
OL,10,Fpeople".
OL,12,F"The outpouring to me and my family in
OL,13,Fthe last three months has shown us
OL,14,Fthat it wasn't just the podcast they
OL,15,Floved, it was Michael too," she said.
OL,17,F"His warmth and his guidance, but
OL,18,Fmainly they connected with Michael
OL,19,Fbecause they saw he was a really
OL,20,Fgenuinely kind person. Unassuming and
OL,21,Fgenuinely caring, that was Michael."
